    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Project Title: {{ $('Github Trigger1').item.json.body.issue.title }}\nProject Details: {{ $('Github Trigger1').item.json.body.issue.body }}\nUser Feedback/Label: {{ $('Github Trigger1').item.json.body.label ? $('Github Trigger1').item.json.body.label.name : $('Github Trigger1').item.json.body.comment.body }}\n\nCURRENT USER PREFERENCES JSON:\n{{ JSON.stringify($json) }}\n",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "You are an AI Memory Integrator. Your job is to process incoming User Feedback and maintain the CURRENT USER PREFERENCES JSON in a highly compacted, de-duplicated state.  \n\nPHASE 1: EXTRACTION 1. Determine the target array (\"positive_preferences\" for positive feedback, \"negative_constraints\" for negative feedback or rejections). 2. Write a 1-sentence summary of the new Project Details. 3. Extract or infer the reason for the feedback.  \n\nPHASE 2: GLOBAL DE-DUPLICATION (CRITICAL) Before you inject the new feedback, you MUST analyze the ENTIRE existing CURRENT USER PREFERENCES JSON and perform a cleanup: 4. Scan the existing \"positive_preferences\" array. If ANY historical items share a similar reason or core concept (e.g., multiple items about \"MCP projects\", or \"conceptual lessons\"), you MUST merge them into a SINGLE item.     - Add their weights together (e.g., 1 + 1 + 1 = 3).    - Write a broader \"item\" description that covers the merged projects. 5. Do the exact same deduplication scan for the existing \"negative_constraints\" array (e.g., merge all items about \"Unit Testing\").  \n\nPHASE 3: INJECT NEW FEEDBACK 6. Compare your Phase 1 extracted feedback against your newly compacted arrays.  7. If the new feedback matches one of your compacted items, increment its weight by +1.  8. If it is entirely unique, append it as a new object with weight: 1.  \n\nOUTPUT FORMAT: Output ONLY a valid JSON object representing the FULLY COMPACTED and UPDATED file state, containing both the \"positive_preferences\" and \"negative_constraints\" arrays. Do not use markdown blocks like ```json.  CURRENT USER PREFERENCES JSON: {{ JSON.stringify($json, null, 2) }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
